 :spec/constraints
 ["Detectors stay pure reducers — observe takes (state, observation) and returns a state map with new anomalies appended; no detector reads from the event log, the registry, or any external state during observe"
  "Per-event detector overhead in the criterium benchmark stays under 5ms across the framework's default detector set ([:tool-loop :repair-loop]) on a recorded event-fixture from the event-log-tool-visibility dogfood (Stage 1 budget, preserved)"
  "Anomaly evidence remains bounded per Stage 1: summary + event-id pointers + fingerprint + threshold metadata + :raw-log-ref. No raw tool args, raw assistant text, or raw file content in evidence — verified by an extension of Stage 1's fuzzer test that injects synthetic 'secret-shaped' content into agent inputs and asserts no synthetic strings appear in any emitted anomaly"
  "Tool fingerprint dimensions come from the tool capability registry (Stage 1's tool-profile API), not from per-detector logic. Adding a new tool to the registry must NOT require a code change in any detector"
  "PR #762's review-fingerprint behavior is preserved end-to-end after the port to :detector/repair-loop — same anomaly category (:anomalies.review/stagnation), same termination semantics, verified by porting PR #762's existing regression tests to the detector test ns and asserting they pass without modification beyond namespace changes"
  "Removing all detectors must still leave Layer 1 (cost / token / turn / liveness) caps enforced — Stage 2 detectors are additive guards, not the only safety net"
  "Mechanical anomalies default to supervisor action :terminate. Heuristic anomalies default to :warn (logged, no action). The full per-category :on-anomaly policy map is explicitly Stage 3"
  "Anomaly composition (multiple anomalies in the same turn) follows the Stage 1 deterministic rule: all anomalies recorded, supervisor selects one controlling anomaly using :fatal>:error>:warn>:info, ties broken :mechanical>:heuristic, further ties broken by earliest :event/seq. The full composite-rules system is Stage 3"
  "Tool profile registration happens at the vendoring component's load time — adapter-claude-code registers Read/Bash/Grep/Glob/Edit/Write/WebSearch/WebFetch in its own ns, not in progress-detector. progress-detector ships zero hardcoded profile data"
  "Event envelope assigns :event/seq monotonically per agent run, NOT globally. Two concurrent agent runs each emit their own seq starting from 0 — no cross-run sequence collision"
  ":resource/version-hash is computed only for tool classes that read/write a resource — absence is meaningful (the tool has no meaningful resource), not an error"
  "Detector wiring is agent-agnostic. The same agent.invoke code path serves planner / implementer / reviewer / tester — per-agent detector overlays come from each agent's prompt EDN, not from N copies of the wiring"
  "Reviewer's existing fingerprint helpers (review-fingerprint, stagnated?, actionable-severities, issue-fingerprint, failed-gate-fingerprint) are MOVED to progress-detector, not duplicated. The reviewer namespace ends Stage 2 with zero local copies of fingerprint logic"]

 :spec/acceptance-criteria
 [;; Event envelope
  "Every tool-call agent event entering the detector pipeline is normalized to the Stage 1 Observation schema (:tool/id, :seq, :timestamp, :tool/duration-ms, :tool/input, :tool/output, :tool/error?, optional :resource/version-hash) — verified by a property test over a recorded fixture of the event-log-tool-visibility dogfood's event sequence asserting every Observation validates against the schema"
  ":event/seq is monotonic per agent run and starts at 0 — verified by an integration test that runs two concurrent fake agent runs and asserts each one's seq starts at 0 and increases monotonically without cross-run collision"
  ":resource/version-hash is present on filesystem reads/writes and absent on tools without a meaningful resource — verified by integration tests over Read/Edit/Write (present) and WebSearch (absent)"

  ;; Tool profile contributions
  "components/adapter-claude-code registers tool profiles for Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write, WebSearch, WebFetch at component load — verified by a load-order test that asserts (tool-profile/lookup :tool/read) returns a non-nil ToolProfile after adapter-claude-code is loaded and nil before"
  "Tool profile registration is idempotent — calling register-profiles! twice does not corrupt the registry or duplicate entries — verified by unit test"
  "components/progress-detector ships ZERO hardcoded tool profile data — verified by a structural test that scans progress-detector's resources and asserts no tool-profile-shaped EDN is present"

  ;; :detector/tool-loop, mechanical positives
  ":detector/tool-loop fires :anomalies.agent/tool-loop (class :mechanical, severity :error) when an agent calls Read on the same path 6 times AND :resource/version-hash is unchanged each time — integration test"
  ":detector/tool-loop fires :class :mechanical when an agent calls Bash with the same command 6 times AND :tool/error? is true on every call AND the failure-fingerprint stub matches each time — integration test"
  ":detector/tool-loop fires :class :mechanical when an agent calls Glob with the same pattern 6 times AND the matched-paths hash is unchanged — integration test"

  ;; :detector/tool-loop, mechanical negatives
  ":detector/tool-loop does NOT fire when an agent re-reads a file after Edit changes its :resource/version-hash (different fingerprint) — integration test"
  ":detector/tool-loop does NOT fire when an agent calls Read on 6 different files (distinct fingerprints) — integration test"
  ":detector/tool-loop does NOT fire when Bash calls share the command but the failure-fingerprint stub differs between runs — integration test"
  ":detector/tool-loop emits :class :heuristic (not :mechanical) for repeated WebSearch calls — :determinism :unstable disqualifies mechanical termination — integration test"

  ;; :detector/repair-loop port
  "PR #762's existing review-stagnation regression tests, ported to the new detector test ns, pass without modification beyond namespace changes — diff between old and new test files shows only ns renames and require-list updates"
  "agent.reviewer no longer contains review-fingerprint, stagnated?, actionable-severities, issue-fingerprint, or failed-gate-fingerprint — verified by a structural test that grep-asserts those symbols are absent from agent/src/ai/miniforge/agent/reviewer.clj"
  ":detector/repair-loop emits :anomalies.review/stagnation (class :mechanical, severity :error) when consecutive review fingerprints match exactly — integration test using the same fixture as the ported PR #762 tests"

  ;; Minimal supervisor
  "An agent run that triggers a mechanical anomaly is terminated by the supervisor — the in-flight LLM stream is cancelled, the controlling anomaly is recorded in the run's event log with the full Stage 1 schema (:category, :class, :severity, :detector/kind, :detector/version, :evidence) — integration test"
  "An agent run that triggers a heuristic anomaly is logged but NOT terminated — verified by integration test that asserts the LLM call completes and the anomaly is present in the event log with :class :heuristic"
  "When multiple anomalies fire in the same observation step, all are recorded; the controlling anomaly is selected via :fatal>:error>:warn>:info, ties broken :mechanical>:heuristic, further ties broken by earliest :event/seq — verified by a property test that constructs anomaly sets with deliberate ties at every level and asserts the selection is reproducible"
  "Removing all detectors from the configured set leaves the agent runtime functional and bounded by Layer 1 (cost/token/turn/liveness) caps only — integration test"

  ;; Agent-runtime wiring
  "agent.invoke (LLM-bearing path) builds the per-agent detector pipeline from layered config (:detectors/defaults + per-agent overlay from prompt EDN) and feeds every parsed agent event through the pipeline — verified by integration test that captures the supervisor's seen-anomalies for a recorded event sequence and asserts the expected anomaly fires"
  "Per-agent detector overlays come from each agent's prompt EDN — a planner with prompt :detectors {:disable [:tool-loop]} does not fire that detector; a tester with :detectors {:tune {:tool-loop {:threshold-n 8}}} uses the bumped threshold — integration test per overlay shape"
  "Wiring is shared across planner / implementer / reviewer / tester — a code search asserts a single agent.invoke detector-wiring code path, not per-agent copies"

  ;; Performance
  "Per-event detector overhead in the criterium benchmark stays under 5ms total across :tool-loop and :repair-loop on the event-log-tool-visibility dogfood event-fixture — verified by a benchmark test that fails on regression"

  ;; Evidence bounding
  "Anomaly :evidence does not contain raw tool args, raw assistant text, or raw file content — verified by extending Stage 1's fuzzer to inject 'secret-shaped' values into Bash command args, Read result content, and Edit patch text and asserting none of those strings appear in any emitted anomaly's evidence"

  ;; Dogfood viability
  "A dogfood run on event-log-tool-visibility EITHER (a) completes through the full SDLC, OR (b) terminates with a detector-emitted anomaly that names which detector fired and includes reproducible evidence — never a bare wallclock stagnation timeout from :prompt/progress-monitor (those become true Layer 1 :liveness watchdogs in Stage 3, but Stage 2 already replaces the within-turn loop case with named anomalies)"]

