 :spec/priority
 {:tier        :critical
  :axes        #{:agent-quality :dogfood-enabler :supervision}
  :theme       :semantic-supervision
  :rationale   "Stage 1 shipped substrate but no firing detectors. The threshold-bump cycle (#779/#781/#782/#783) is still the operative supervision mechanism. Stage 2 turns the substrate on: tool-loop and repair-loop fire on real agent events; the supervisor terminates on mechanical anomalies; reviewer's local fingerprint code consolidates into one component. Without Stage 2, Stage 1 is dead weight. Stage 3 (phase contracts, full :on-anomaly map, liveness rename) sits on top of a working detection pipeline — building it without Stage 2 would mean designing policy for a system that does not yet emit the events policy reacts to."
  :blocks      ["agent-stream-watchdog-and-resume.spec.edn"]
  :blocked-by  ["progress-detector-semantic-loop-detection.spec.edn"]}

 :spec/workflow-type :canonical-sdlc}
